# Role: user-account-engineer

> **Owns:** Admin-side user management (list users, assign roles, activate/deactivate accounts) and each user's own profile (view/update name, avatar, contact details).
> Do not create or modify files outside the Owned Paths below without a PR reviewed by someone currently holding this role.

## Role Charter
This role covers both sides of "account" data: the Admin console view of all users, and the individual's self-service profile page. It does not own login/session (`authentication-engineer`) or role-gate enforcement mechanics (`authorization-engineer`) — it only owns the business rules around *who can change what on a user record*.

## Owned Paths
```
src/controllers/userController.ts
src/controllers/profileController.ts
src/services/userService.ts
src/services/profileService.ts
src/repositories/userRepository.ts
src/routes/usersRoutes.ts
src/app/(dashboard)/profile/page.tsx
src/app/(dashboard)/admin/users/page.tsx
src/components/profile/
src/components/admin/UserManagementTable.tsx
```

## Project Context
- Stack: Next.js + TypeScript (FE), Express + TypeScript (BE), Neon PostgreSQL
- Architecture: Controller → Service → Repository (strict separation)
- Auth: import `authenticate` from `authentication-engineer`'s middleware and `requireRole` from `authorization-engineer`'s middleware — never rewrite either.
- API prefix: `/api/v1/`

## Strict Rules
1. Only **Admin** role can change user roles or activate/deactivate accounts — log every role change to `role_change_logs`.
2. A user cannot deactivate their own account.
3. Deactivated users are denied at login — that check itself lives in `authentication-engineer`'s `AuthService`, but the `isActive` flag is this role's data to own.
4. Identity data (name, email) lives in `neon_auth.users`; email is read-only through the profile endpoint — never allow email updates through `updateProfile`.
5. Updatable profile fields: `name`, `avatar_url`, `contact_details` only.
6. Role options are fixed: `'Admin'` | `'Reviewer'` | `'User'`.

```typescript
// src/services/userService.ts
async changeRole(targetUserId: string, newRole: UserRole, requestingUserId: string): Promise<User> {
  const requester = await userRepository.findById(requestingUserId);
  if (requester?.role !== 'Admin') {
    throw new AppError('Only Admins can change user roles', 403);
  }
  const target = await userRepository.findById(targetUserId);
  if (!target) throw new AppError('User not found', 404);
  return userRepository.updateRole(targetUserId, newRole);
}

async toggleStatus(targetUserId: string, isActive: boolean, requestingUserId: string): Promise<User> {
  if (targetUserId === requestingUserId) {
    throw new AppError('Cannot change your own account status', 400);
  }
  return userRepository.updateStatus(targetUserId, isActive);
}
```

```typescript
// src/services/profileService.ts
async updateProfile(userId: string, updates: ProfileUpdateInput): Promise<UserProfile> {
  // Never allow email/role/isActive update through this endpoint
  const { email, role, isActive, ...safeUpdates } = updates as any;
  return userRepository.updateProfile(userId, safeUpdates);
}
```

## Admin User Management Page
- Table: Name | Email | Role | Status | Actions
- Actions: Change Role (dropdown) · Activate/Deactivate toggle
- Show a `<ConfirmationModal>` (shared component, see `03-frontend-conventions.mdc`) before role change or deactivation.

